📊 Case Study  – SIOP Reporting (Data Handling & Dashboard)

📌 Project Overview

In Sales, Inventory & Operations Planning (SIOP), forecast data is generated periodically and stored as monthly snapshots. Each snapshot represents an “As Of Period” when the forecast was created, along with future forecast periods.

The objective of this project is to transform snapshot-based forecast data into a structured format so that multiple forecast versions can be compared side by side for analysis.

🎯 Objective
Convert multiple forecast snapshots into a lag-based structure
Enable comparison of forecasts across time periods
Build a scalable dataset for Power BI reporting and analysis
Support executive-level decision-making for Revenue, Non-Revenue, and Capex

⚙️ Data Transformation Logic

Forecast snapshots are categorized into:

Resultant → Latest forecast snapshot (e.g., 2023 P12)
Lag 0 → Previous snapshot (e.g., 2023 P11)
Lag 1 → Snapshot before Lag 0 (e.g., 2023 P10)



Each forecast type is split into separate columns:

Resultant Revenue / Non-Revenue / Capex Forecast
Lag 0 Revenue / Non-Revenue / Capex Forecast
Lag 1 Revenue / Non-Revenue / Capex Forecast
📐 KPI Formulas
1. Forecast Accuracy %
1 - ABS(Lag Qty - Actual Qty) / Actual Qty
2. Forecast Bias %
(Lag Qty - Actual Qty) / Actual Qty
